- "golden geese" metaphorically refers to the top customers who generate significant revenue;
- "laid the most eggs" symbolically represents the highest amount of revenue that customers have generated;
- "past month" refers to the last 30 days;
- "golden eggs" is a metaphor for the total revenue that these customers have contributed;
- "type of currency" corresponds to the currency in which their orders were placed.
